Hashlock is a program designed to allow for the user to memorize one single password and have all of their other passwords generated for them. The system also tries to be as extensible as possible trying to add support for.

Firefox Extention
Chrome Extention
Safari Extention
Android App
iPhone App
iPad App
Terminal Program
Windows Standalone GUI
Linux Standalone GUI
Mac Standalone GUI

The core system it written in C++ so that it is easy to maintain. Inside the core system there is

A c++ library function for generating the hashed passwords
a JSON object for the different modes the function can use

hashlock(string masterPassword, string accountName, int type)